The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, held a press briefing on June 2, 2014. He began by discussing the Obama administration's focus on attracting job-creating investment to America. He highlighted a recent study by A.T. Kearney that ranked the U.S. as the top destination in the world for foreign direct investment. Carney then took questions from reporters on various topics including the release of Sergeant Bowe Bergdahl and the new carbon rule proposed by the EPA.